events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Miami Heat

headlines.description: — Jimmy Butler scored 28 points to lead the Miami Heat past the depleted Los Angeles Lakers 110-104 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Butler scores 28, Heat beat depleted Lakers 110-104

headlines.description: — Nikola Vucevic and Zach Levine each scored 22 points and the Chicago Bulls beat the Toronto Raptors 122-133 on Thursday night for their third straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: LaVine, Vucevic lead Bulls past Raptors, 122-113

events.name: Cleveland Cavaliers at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Collin Sexton scored 27 points and the Cleveland Cavaliers ended a five-game series losing streak to Oklahoma City, beating the Thunder 129-102 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sexton scores 27 points, Cavaliers beat Thunder 129-102

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic scored 27 points, Kristaps Porzingis had 26 points and 17 rebounds playing on consecutive days for the first time in two months and the Dallas Mavericks beat the Milwaukee Bucks 116-101 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic, Porzingis lead bounce-back Mavs over Bucks 116-101

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Utah Jazz

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 37 points to lead the Utah Jazz to their 23rd straight home victory, 122-103 victory over the Portland Trail Blazers on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jazz rout Trail Blazers for 23rd straight home victory

headlines.description: — Paul George scored 33 points, Kawhi Leonard added 27 and the Los Angeles Clippers beat the Phoenix Suns 113-103 on Thursday night in a matchup of two of the top teams in the Western Conference.
headlines.shortLinkText: George scores 33 points, Clippers snap Suns' winning streak
